# Block Element Behavior

## Block model

- Every individual element — or any element that contains other elements — is a **block**.
- Everything is made of **fundamental blocks** (primitives, variables, expressions, etc.) composed into larger blocks.
- **Function body** (Main Function / Function): tapping a **minimized chip** opens its **Block Editor** ([`BlockEditorPanel.tsx`](src/components/panels/BlockEditorPanel.tsx)).
- **Block editors** show the block's **full UI**; nested children stay **minimized chips**; tapping a chip opens **another** editor on the stack ([`editorStack`](src/App.tsx)). This repeats recursively.

## Core rules

- Start: **Main Function only** → [`emptyProgram.ts`](src/constants/emptyProgram.ts). Main cannot be deleted/nested.
- Every slot needs `slotTarget` on [`BlockSlot.tsx`](src/components/ui/BlockSlot.tsx) or drag-drop is dead.
- Invalid drop → red dashed border + message. Never silent reject. Primitives auto-coerce to slot type.

## Blocks & nesting

**Tree:** Program = top-level canvas blocks ([`placements`](src/types/program.ts)) + nested children in parent `data` (body arrays, value slots, operands) — CRUD in [`blockTree.ts`](src/lib/program/blockTree.ts).

| Context | Renders as | Where |
|---------|------------|-------|
| Top-level canvas | Full block + drag handle | [`WorkspaceCanvas.tsx`](src/components/layout/WorkspaceCanvas.tsx) → [`BlockRenderer`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx) |
| Statement body child | **Minimized chip** (`nestedView: true`) | [`StatementBody.tsx`](src/components/blocks/StatementBody.tsx) |
| Value inside slot (in body) | **Chip** | Print/If pass `nestedView: true` to `renderChild` |
| Value inside slot (in editor) | **Full UI** | Expression/For/While pass `nestedView: false` in editor panel |
| `valueRef` | **ValueRefChip** (not minimized block) | [`BlockRenderer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx) |

**`BlockRenderer` rule:** `nestedView && kind !== 'main'` → [`MinimizedBlockChip`](src/components/blocks/MinimizedBlockChip.tsx). Otherwise → full block component. See `renderChild` opts in [`BlockRenderer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx).

**Editor stack:** Click chip → `openBlockEditor` → [`BlockEditorPanel`](src/components/panels/BlockEditorPanel.tsx) (full UI; nested children stay chips). Multiple editors stack ([`editorStack`](src/App.tsx)). Chip **×** or panel remove → [`detachNestedBlock`](src/hooks/useEditorState.ts) (discards nested block).

**Never** render full nested block UI inline inside a parent on canvas — chips only.

## Where to drop (workflow)

| Step | Action | Block / slot |
|------|--------|--------------|
| 1 | Statement | Variable → `statement-body` |
| 2 | Value | Constant → Variable `variable-value` (not body) |
| 3 | Expression | Expression → body → editor → `expression-operand` left/right |
| 4 | Loops | For/While → body → editor → `for-init` / `for-condition` / `for-increment` / `while-condition` |

Containers grow vertically when a valid child is placed.

## Typed value matching

Value-producing blocks: **primitive**, **variable**, **expression**, **functionCall**, **valueRef**.

- Read type via `getBlockValueType` / `getValueTypeFromSource` in [`typeChecker.ts`](src/lib/validation/typeChecker.ts) and [`scope.ts`](src/lib/program/scope.ts).
- Typed slots accept a block when `canValueSlotAcceptBlock(expected, block)` is true: `getBlockValueType(block) === expected`.
- **Primitives** always fit typed slots; coerce to slot type on attach (`defaultValueForType`).
- **Block drag** onto a value slot → nest/move the block (detach from old location via `attachBlockIdToSlot`).
- **Reference grip** / scope picker → `valueRef` only; source stays on its line (`assignReferenceToSlot`).

## Slot acceptance → [`typeChecker.ts`](src/lib/validation/typeChecker.ts)

| Slot | Accepts |
|------|---------|
| `statement-body` | variable, expression, print, functionCall, if, for, while — **not** primitive |
| `variable-value` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef — type must match `valueType` |
| `print-value` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef (any value type) |
| `if-condition` | boolean-valued blocks/refs (`canBooleanSlotAcceptBlock`) |
| `expression-operand` | value nestable kinds — match operand type (`getExpressionOperandType`; comparisons use **number** operands) |
| `for-init` / `for-increment` | number-valued blocks/refs |
| `for-condition` / `while-condition` | boolean-valued blocks/refs |
| `call-arg` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef — type must match arg |
| `type-variable` | variable only |
| `function-signature` | type block only |

## In-scope refs

- Link keeps source on its line; consumer stores `valueRef`. **Use existing…** on empty slots (`scopeConsumerId`).
- Drag **ReferencePill** / link grip → value slot (not block drag). Usage edges in body ([`ConnectionLayer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/ConnectionLayer.tsx)). Source removal → error on ref.

